## Typography

### Font Roles

**Logo – Palatino (alternative: Cormorant Garamond or Lora):**
- Large, prominent. Primary color (celeste neónsito / `--color-primary`) on black background.
- Soft glow or highlights using `--color-primary-light`; avoid long texts.
- Load via `next/font/google` as `Cormorant Garamond` or `Lora`.

**Titles – Michroma:**
- Medium–large size, high impact. Primary color (celeste neónsito / `--color-primary`) on black background.
- For banners, highlighted sections, H1/H2.
- The celeste neon glow on black creates the desired "medium neon" effect.
- Load via `next/font/google` as `Michroma`.

**Subtitles – Lovelo (alternative: Exo 2 or Nunito):**
- Medium size, visual balance. Primary color (celeste neónsito / `--color-primary`) on black background.
- For CTAs, menus, cards; no strong glow to avoid competing with titles.
- Load via `next/font/google` as `Exo 2` or `Nunito`.

**Body – Roboto:**
- 16–18px web size. White (#FFFFFF) or light gray (#E0E0E0) on black background.
- No light effects; primary color accents only on keywords or links.
- Load via `next/font/google` as `Roboto`.

### Typography Hierarchy

- Logo → sophistication
- Titles → futuristic impact
- Subtitles → balance
- Body → readability

**Rule:** Do not use all typography styles in the same block; "less is more".

### Implementation

Use utility classes: `font-logo`, `font-title`, `font-subtitle`, `font-body`, and sizes like `text-title-lg`, `text-title-md`, `text-subtitle`, `text-body`.

