## General Style Guidelines

### Background
- Pure black (#000000) as mandatory base. Highlights neon colors.

### Primary Color (Celeste Neónsito)
- Important landing color. Must be in the **primary group** (`--color-primary` and variations) centralized in `globals.css` to facilitate constant changes.
- Use with moderation for maximum impact: main buttons, highlighted titles, borders/glows on interactive elements.
- The celeste neon glow on black creates the "medium neon" effect the client seeks.

### Gradients and Glow
- Only on titles, main buttons, or key elements. The celeste neon glow on black is the desired effect. Avoid saturation.

### Particles/Spirals
- If added later, combine with Michroma (titles), not with Roboto (body).

### Contrast
- White texts (#FFFFFF) or light grays (#E0E0E0) on black ensure readability. Celeste neon on black has high contrast.
- Review WCAG where applicable.

### Flexibility
- The primary group must be easy to modify. Changing `--color-primary` in `globals.css` should automatically update all components using `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-primary`, etc.

