## Consistency Rules

1. **Background:** Pure black (#000000 / `--color-bg`) as mandatory base throughout the application. Only use `--color-bg-secondary` (#0A0A0A) if subtle contrast is needed in cards/sections, but keep black as dominant.

2. **Primary Color:** Use celeste neónsito with moderation: main buttons, highlighted titles, borders/glows on interactive elements. The "medium neon" effect comes from celeste neon contrast on black.

3. **Gradients and Glow:** Only on titles (Michroma), CTA buttons, or key elements. The celeste neon glow on black is the desired effect. Avoid saturation.

4. **Text:** White (#FFFFFF) for titles/main, light gray (#E0E0E0/#B0B0B0) for body. Ensures readability on black.

5. **Contrast:** White/gray texts on black have high contrast. Celeste neon on black also has high contrast. Review WCAG where applicable.

6. **Flexibility:** The primary group must be easy to modify. Changing `--color-primary` in `globals.css` should automatically update all components using `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-primary`, etc.

